  "prompt": "How do I change gender in booked IRCTC e-tickets?",
  "response": "Changing the gender details on a booked IRCTC e-ticket typically requires specific steps, as personal information like gender is considered critical for accurate passenger records. Here's how you can attempt to make this change:\n\n### **1. Check IRCTC's Policy**\nBefore proceeding, it's essential to understand that IRCTC does not generally allow modifications to passenger details (including gender) after the ticket has been booked. However, in certain cases, you might have options depending on the ticket status and time remaining before the journey.\n\n### **2. Cancellation and Rebooking (If Possible)**\nIf changing gender is not directly permitted, the most straightforward method is to cancel the existing ticket and book a new one with the correct details. Here's how:\n\n#### **a. Cancellation Steps:**\n1. **Log in to Your IRCTC Account:**\n   - Visit the [IRCTC website](https://www.irctc.co.in/) and sign in using your credentials.\n   \n2. **Navigate to 'Booked Tickets':**\n   - Go to the \"Booked Ticket History\" section.\n\n3. **Select the Ticket to Cancel:**\n   - Choose the ticket for which you want to change the gender details.\n\n4. **Initiate Cancellation:**\n   - Click on the \"Cancel Ticket\" option and follow the prompts to complete the cancellation process.\n   \n5. **Check Refund Details:**\n   - Ensure you understand the cancellation charges and the refund amount you'll receive.\n\n#### **b. Rebooking a New Ticket:**\n1. **Wait for Refund Confirmation:**\n   - Ensure that the cancellation refund is processed to your account.\n\n2. **Book a New Ticket:**\n   - Proceed to book a new ticket, this time entering the correct gender information for the passenger.\n\n### **3. Contact IRCTC Customer Support**\nIf cancellation and rebooking are not feasible (e.g., due to technological constraints, time limitations, or personal preferences), you can reach out directly to IRCTC's customer support for assistance:\n\n- **Phone Support:**\n  - Call the IRCTC helpline number: [IRCTC Customer Care](https://www.irctc.co.in/nget/train-search) to get the latest contact details.\n\n- **Email Support:**\n  - Send a detailed email explaining your request to [IRCTC's official email](mailto:your-email@irctc.co.in) (please verify the correct email address from the official website).\n\n- **Visit a Railway Reservation Counter:**\n  - Go to the nearest railway reservation office with your ticket and a valid ID proof to request the change in person.\n\n### **4. Important Considerations**\n- **Time Constraints:**\n  - Changes or cancellations usually need to be made within a specific timeframe before the scheduled departure of the train.\n\n- **Fare Differences:**\n  - If there's a difference in fare for the new booking, you may need to pay the additional amount or receive a refund if applicable.\n\n- **Proof of Identity:**\n  - Ensure that the ID proof you provide matches the details in the ticket for a smooth modification process.\n\n- **Non-Refundable Tickets:**\n  - Some tickets may have restrictions on cancellations or modifications, so reviewing the ticket terms is crucial.\n\n### **5. Preventive Measures for Future Bookings**\nTo avoid similar issues in the future:\n\n- **Double-Check Details:**\n  - Always verify all passenger details, including gender, before finalizing the booking.\n\n- **Use Auto-Fill Carefully:**\n  - If using saved information or auto-fill features, ensure that the correct details are entered for each passenger.\n\n- **Contact Support Before Booking:**\n  - If uncertain about any details, contact IRCTC support before confirming the ticket.\n\n### **Conclusion**\nWhile IRCTC does not provide a direct option to change the gender on a booked e-ticket, the most viable solution is to cancel the existing ticket and rebook it with the correct information. Always make sure to review all passenger details carefully during the booking process to minimize the need for such changes.\n\nIf you encounter any difficulties or have specific circumstances, reaching out to IRCTC customer support is the best course of action to explore available options.",
